    "summary": "PubNub exposes HTTP APIs for real-time messaging, account administration, and Insights metrics, plus a hosted MCP server and a local MCP CLI package; documented auth uses Service Integration API keys or hosted MCP OAuth.",
    "description": "PubNub is a real-time communications platform for building live, interactive applications with publish/subscribe messaging, presence, and related services. It also provides account-management, analytics, and AI-assistant integration capabilities through its admin, insights, and MCP offerings.",
    "credentials": {
      "pubnub_service_api_key": {
        "type": "api_key",
        "label": "PubNub Service Integration API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://admin.pubnub.com/service-integrations",
        "setup": "Sign in to the [PubNub Admin Portal](https://admin.pubnub.com/login) as an Owner or Account Admin, then open [API Management / Service Integrations](https://admin.pubnub.com/service-integrations). Create a Service Integration or open an existing one, choose **Generate API Key**, set its expiration, and copy the key when it is shown. PubNub states the key is shown only once; if lost, generate a new one and revoke the old key. See [Service Integrations and API Keys](https://www.pubnub.com/docs/portal/service-integrations) and the [Admin API intro](https://www.pubnub.com/docs/admin-api)."
      },
